call.transcript:
Agent: Hello, this is Hannah from Fetch Recruitment. This call is recorded for quality and training purposes. How can I help you today?
User: i didn't get paid
Agent: I can help with payroll enquiries. Are you calling because you’re having trouble with the payroll system, or would you like me to log an enquiry with the payroll team?
User: log enquiry
Agent: Okay, I can send this as an enquiry to the payroll team. To start, could you please tell me a little about the problem?
User: i didn' get paid i said
Agent: I understand you didn't get paid. Could you please provide a bit more detail about the issue? For example, what pay period are you referring to, or have you submitted your timesheet?
User: this month
Agent: Thanks for clarifying. And just to confirm, do you deal with our Melbourne or Perth office?
User: perth
Agent: So I can send this through to the payroll team, I’ll just need a few details. What’s your full name?
User: perth name
Agent: I'm sorry, I didn't quite catch that. Could you please tell me your full name again?
User: wilson man
Agent: Thanks, Wilson. And what's your best phone number?
User: 0412123123
Agent: And your email address?
User: wilson@email.com
Agent: Let me read that back to make sure I’ve got it right. Your name is Wilson Man, your phone number is 0412123123, your email is wilson@email.com, and you’re reporting that you didn't get paid this month for our Perth office. Does that all sound correct, and is it okay if I log this for the team?
User: yes
